# ~/.claude is a folded symlink into this repo, so Claude Code writes ALL of its
# runtime state here: session transcripts, shell-env snapshots, config backups
# (.claude.json contains OAuth tokens), prompt history, caches, IDE lockfiles.
# Much of it is machine-local and some contains secrets.
#
# Posture: default-deny. Ignore everything, then re-include only curated config.
# This stays safe even when a future Claude Code version writes a new artifact
# type we haven't seen yet.

# Ignore everything...
*
# ...but let git descend into directories so curated nested files are reachable
# (e.g. skills/<name>/SKILL.md). Files inside runtime dirs stay ignored because
# nothing below re-includes them.
!*/

# Curated, version-controlled config (anchored to .claude/ root with a leading
# slash so a stray same-named file in a runtime dir can't be un-ignored).
!/.gitignore
!/CLAUDE.md
!/CONNECTORS.md
!/settings.json
!/agents/**
!/commands/**
!/skills/**

# Explicitly machine-local (kept ignored even if a rule above ever loosens):
#   settings.local.json  - per-machine permission overrides (Claude Code convention)
